The program AxisFinder was designed to find the crystallographic axes in a segmented detector using segment occupancy and transverse anisotropy in the crystal.
For the algorithm and more details, see
Eur. Phys. J. C  72  (2012) 1950
(link http://www.springerlink.com/content/yw37xk4263734358/)

The GIT version contains source code only, in ~volynets/Work/someplace  you will find all the plots that were produced using the program to match the script and the output
